FIGURE 3.
Adult morphology of 

Pygospio elegans

from Broad Bay, Nahant, Massachusetts, U.S.A. (USNM 177011– 177016). A, anterior end of a female, left lateral view, showing spoon-like hooded hooks starting in neuropodia from chaetiger 8, and bidentate hooks starting from chaetiger 13. B, same, dorsal view of anterior end, showing composition of head and onerow nototrochs starting from chaetiger 2; palps missing. C, chaetiger 13 of a male, dorsal view, showing double-row nototroch extending onto branchia, and notopodial postchaetal lamellae fused to branchiae. D, posterior end, dorsal view, showing pygidium with two pairs of cirri. E, chaetigers 7 and 8, left lateral view. F, chaetiger 8, left lateral view, showing spoon-like hooded hooks in neuropodium. Abbreviations: 
br
—branchia; 
ca
—caruncle; 
dc
—dorsal pygidial cirrus; 
lo
—lateral sensory ciliated organ; 
no
—notopodial postchaetal lamella; 
nt
—nototroch; 
nu
—nuchal organ; 
pa
—palp scar; 
pe
—peristomium; 
pr
— prostomium; 
s8, s13
—chaetigers 8, 13; 
vc
—ventral pygidial cirri. Scale bars: A—100 µm. B—50 µm. C–E—30 µm. F—10 µm.
